==English==

===Noun===
'''calipers'''

# {{italbrac|usually plural only}} A device used to [[measure]] very small items or measure items [[very]] [[precisely]].
#:'''1902''' '' "Good, good for there," he mumbled, and then with a certain eagerness asked me whether I would let him measure my head. Rather surprised, I said Yes, when he produced a thing like '''calipers''' and got the dimensions back and front and every way, taking notes carefully.'' — Joseph Conrad, ''[http://etext.virginia.edu/etcbin/ot2www-pubeng?specfile=/texts/english/modeng/publicsearch/modengpub.o2w&act=surround&offset=171491698&tag=Conrad,+Joseph,+1857-1924:+Heart+of+Darkness,+1902&query=calipers&id=ConDark Heart of Darkness.]''

